Merge pull request #48 from ChALkeR/master

Build leaking strings with push/join instead of string concatenation. Slightly slower on some browsers but consumes far less memory.
Build leaking strings with push/join instead of string concatenation. Solves #46.

Optimization of Base64 and URISafe compression and decompression methods.

This breaks the binary compatibility of the compression, meaning the same string can have a different compressed base64 version. Both the new and the old versions of the library are able to decompress both compressed versions though. The tests have been updated accordingly.

Optimization of UTF16 compression and decompression methods

Do not use a second pass anymore, directly call the _compress and _decompress methods
Parametrized compress and decompress (with private versions) to allow UTF16 and Base64 to be compressed without an extra pass of re-encoding

More tests.

Also split the binary compatibility tests btw compression and decompression tests. Compression tests are here for information while decompression tests MUST pass on any subsequent release.
Applied changes to the minified version

Bugfix in compressToEncodedURIComponent and the associated decompress method.

Added two new methods:

compressToEncodedURIComponent: compress into a string that is already URI encoded

decompressFromEncodedURIComponent: the associated decompress method

Release version 1.3.4

This version contains two new methods:

compressToUint8Array: compress into uint8array (UCS-2 big endian format)
decompressFromUint8Array: the associated decompression function

Merge pull request #15 from J0eCool/master

Add a sanity check to partially-correct input

Add a sanity check to partially-correct input

I was generating compressed base64 strings of the form "abc/def". I
accidentally tried decompressing just the "abc" portion of the string,
causing decompress() to hang indefinitely. This index/length check
prevents that case.
